er father,\nSt. John .Smith, wealthy New\nYork broker, declared today he\nwould view the picture of a pretty\ngirl amnesia vidtim in Cincinnati.\nPolice there reported the girl re\nsembled the Smith College stu\ndent, whose disappearance in 1328\nevoked a nation-wide hunt.\nHowever, St. John Smith was\nconvinced the body of a girl found\nin the Long Meadow River in 1929\nand identified through dental\nwork was the body of his ipissing\ndaughter.\nJune Copper Exports\nDrop to 27,493 Tons\nExports of refined copper from\nUnited States in June M were 3T,-\n493 tons, against 34,090 tons in\nMay and 30,376 tons in April, the\nAmerican Bureau of Metal Sta\ntistics reported today.\u2019 Imports\nof copper in unmanufactured\nform by United States were 27,-\n890 tons in June, against 22,294\nin May and 32,186 in April. Great\nBritain imported 15,086 tons in\nJune, against 10,730 tons in May\nand 11.304 tons in April.\nELECTRIC RATES CUT\nSTAUNTON, Va.. July 21.\u2014The\nVirginia Public Service Company\nis announcing a voluntary reduc\ntion in rates tor all classes of\nservice, the sixth in two years. The\nnew schedules will result in aa an\ntiMa MIMMi* MnMaMn BBre\nI f\nTto Hatioaal My\nProduce Markets\nBALTIMORE PRODUCE\nApples\u2014Supp*e< modarxU. i Califor\nnia. boxes. Orawnstelns, fancy.\nn Maryland. Penneyvlatia and\nVirxinfa, bn. baskets. Transparent*, aa\n-..\u2019'Ji' Williams Keda. 7\u00bbc\n0*1.71; Summer ftamboe. larxa *lm.\nmedium. 11*1.2t; various\nother summer varieties iOcatl.te\nNearby, %-bn. hampers various sum\nmer varieties 2SO\u00ab\u00abe.\nBeans\u2014Suppliae moderate. Nearby.\nRound Strfnxless per bu., 7ScA|l.<e.\nBeets\u2014Supplies moderate. Nearby,\nper bunch. Hie.\nBlackberries\u2014Supplies light. Western\nMaryland-and New Aeraey. lt<*7oc Ml.\nCabbage\u2014Supplies light. Virginia.\niee-lb. crates Round type,\nNearby, bu. baaketa, 7Scgfl.lt. tew\nhigher.\nCantaloupes\u2014No car-lot arrivals; 2 re\nconsigned 4 cars on track, including\nbroken. R